<refnamediv><indexterm><primary sortas="restart-hadb">restart-hadb &mdash;  stops and starts the specified HADB database</primary></indexterm><indexterm><primary sortas=" stops and starts the specified HADB database"> stops and starts the specified HADB database &mdash; restart-hadb</primary></indexterm>
<refname>restart-hadb</refname><refpurpose> stops and starts the specified HADB database</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>restart-hadb</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg>&Dash;&Dash;hosts <replaceable>hadb-host-list</replaceable></arg><arg choice="opt"> &Dash;&Dash;haagentport <replaceable>port_number</replaceable> </arg><arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpassword <replaceable>password</replaceable></arg><arg choice="req"> <replaceable>database-name</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>The <command>restart-hadb</command> command stops and restarts the specified HADB database for an application server cluster.</para>
<para>This command is supported in remote mode only.</para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;hosts</option></term><listitem><para>A comma separated list of host names where the HADB instance is configured. The number of hosts must be greater than 1 and must be an even number. The same host names can be repeated. Use fully qualified hostnames
when specifying the hostlist interfaces explicitly for hosts with multiple network interfaces.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;haagentport</option></term><listitem><para>Identifies the number of the HA agent port. The default is 1862.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpassword</option></term><listitem><para>Identifies the HA administrator password.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="narrow">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>database_name </replaceable></term><listitem><para>Name of the HADB database.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
